Currence","startTime":null,"eventDescription":"Who is Rudy Currence? Refreshing but familiar, confident but humble, innovative yet classic, these are just a few words that describe Grammy and Dove Award winning producer, singer-songwriter, Rudy Currence. Truly the world is only beginning to scratch the surface when it comes to who Mike Chek Entertainment Recording Artist Rudy Currence really is. This triple threat singer-songwriter, musician and producer has become what his fans can only summarize as an experience and seeing is believing! After hearing his soulful voice, it’s obvious that Rudy was raised singing in the church. The son of a Pastor and native of Rock Hill, SC, Rudy perfected his craft playing and singing in his father’s church. Graduating from Furman University with a music degree, Rudy has been trained extensively in classical piano and voice, jazz, folk, pop, and R&B.

Although he’s considered a “singer’s singer and a musician’s musician”, Rudy has also established himself as an accomplished songwriter. He’s written songs for R&B/Pop singers Mya and Ray J, “The Bourne Identity” starring Matt Damon, Multi-Platinum Grammy and Emmy award winning producer, Quincy Jones, four-time Grammy Award winning singer/songwriter and national recording artist, Karen Clark-Sheard and multiple Stellar and Grammy Award winning Producer, Donald Lawrence.

A classically trained pianist, Rudy is currently endorsed by Kawai Piano, the 2nd largest piano distributer in the world! In appreciation of his 1st official endorsement (and following the success of his mixtape, 

“DIGITAL ANALOG”, available at www.mikechekent.com), Rudy launched an online web-series called the Kawai Chronicles. “The Chronicles” as Rudy commonly refers to them, have earned him thousands of subscribers and millions of views on www.YouTube.com, and these numbers increase by thousands daily! 

Along with a strong online presence, Rudy has had several national television appearances including ABC’s “The View” and BET’s “106th” and Park”. Rudy continues to tour extensively, and performs at colleges and universities across the U.S. While his artistry is rapidly growing and evolving, he still enjoys the success and fan support gained through his indie albums: “More Than You’ll Ever Know”, “Here With You”, and “Last Christmas” (all available on www.iTunes.com).

Soon the world will learn and love this extraordinary young man known as Rudy Currence. When asked what his aspirations were, Rudy had this to say: “I want to leave a legacy through song. I want to be remembered around the world for having made a positive impact through music. I am a true artist. I will never follow trends but always set them.
